- Among binary features, feature_039=1 differed by -1.535 months versus feature_039=0 (p=<1e-300).
- Standardized continuous-feature contrasts supported feature_044 as favorable (+1.75 months per SD, p=<1e-300) and feature_027 as unfavorable (-0.799 months per SD, p=<1e-300).

Adjusted findings:
- feature_046: adjusted effect 1.101 months, p=<1e-300.
- feature_069: adjusted effect 0.53 months, p=<1e-300.
- feature_004: adjusted effect 0.235 months, p=<1e-300.
- feature_044: adjusted effect 1.749 months, p=<1e-300.
- feature_039: adjusted effect -1.549 months, p=<1e-300.
- feature_027: adjusted effect -0.795 months, p=<1e-300.
- feature_015: adjusted effect -0.985 months, p=<1e-300.
- feature_031: adjusted effect -0.583 months, p=<1e-300.

Threshold findings:
- Highest-quartile feature_044 had +3.009 months versus lower values (p=<1e-300).
- Highest-quartile feature_027 had -1.459 months versus lower values (p=<1e-300).
- feature_044 >= 71.8 showed 3.009 months difference (p=<1e-300).
- feature_044 >= 58.2 showed 2.947 months difference (p=<1e-300).
- feature_044 >= 65 showed 2.826 months difference (p=<1e-300).
- feature_027 >= 1 showed -1.459 months difference (p=<1e-300).

Interaction and subgroup findings:
- feature_046:feature_069 interaction effect 1.591 months, p=<1e-300.
- feature_046:feature_010 interaction effect 1.09 months, p=<1e-300.
- feature_046:feature_025 interaction effect 0.418 months, p=<1e-300.
- feature_046:feature_031 interaction effect -1.624 months, p=<1e-300.
- feature_046:feature_063 interaction effect -1.365 months, p=<1e-300.
- feature_046:feature_062 interaction effect -0.638 months, p=<1e-300.
- feature_046:z(feature_062) subgroup interaction effect -0.638 months, p=<1e-300.
- feature_069:z(feature_062) subgroup interaction effect -0.311 months, p=<1e-300.
- feature_031:z(feature_062) subgroup interaction effect 0.36 months, p=<1e-300.
- feature_063:z(feature_062) subgroup interaction effect 0.255 months, p=<1e-300.

Null/weak probes:
- Threshold feature_044 >= 71.8 (q=0.75) had a mean difference of 3.009 months (n=12600, p=<1e-300).
- Threshold feature_044 >= 58.2 (q=0.25) had a mean difference of 2.947 months (n=37668, p=<1e-300).
- Threshold feature_044 >= 65 (q=0.5) had a mean difference of 2.826 months (n=25044, p=<1e-300).
- Threshold feature_027 >= 1 (q=0.5) had a mean difference of -1.459 months (n=32404, p=<1e-300).
- Threshold feature_027 >= 1 (q=0.75) had a mean difference of -1.459 months (n=32404, p=<1e-300).

Overall conclusion:
The cohort contains several strong feature-outcome associations with pfs_months despite anonymized predictors. The most reproducible signals were the top screened main effects that remained significant in adjusted OLS models. Several interaction terms were statistically significant, suggesting heterogeneity in feature effects across subgroups; however, because feature labels are opaque, these should be treated as pattern-discovery results rather than mechanistic clinical claims. Weak probes with small coefficients and p-values above 0.05 were not supported.

